				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We definately need a Grow Companion spell.  There are many places where a tiny pet will get caught on the world geometry, and not be able to follow it's master.
<br />

<br />
- Stairs in Kael (Gnomes can't walk up these, pets are smaller. <img src="images/smiles/sad10.gif" alt="sad10" border="0" />)
<br />
- In PoTactics, the room upstairs and to the left of the Arena.  No mobs spawn in there, so groups often use it as a place to pull to.  A shrunken pet can't get out of the small depression in the ground there, just keeps running into the edge.
<br />
- Etc, etc, etc.  Basically, any place a Gnome has to jump to get past, a pet will get perminantly stuck.  In fact more than that as the pets are smaller than gnomes.
<br />

<br />
Don't get me wrong, REALLY tiny pets is a cool thing.  Keeps them out of the way of Group and Raid members.  But they either need to learn to jump really high, or we need a pet grow spell.  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_pray.gif" alt="Pray" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=279732" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Kantreach</a> - Arch Mage Antagonist - Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
